data.text:
Cherilyn Sarkisian, (Born: May 20, 1946 (1946-05-20) [age 78]),[1] also known as Cher, is an American singer, actress and television personality. She is referred as the Goddess of Pop.

History[]

Life[]

On May 20, 1946, Cherilyn was born in El Centro, California.

In November 1962, Cherilyn first met Sonny Bono in a Los Angeles coffee shop at age 16.[2]

Music[]

In 1963, Cherilyn started her music career.

In 1964, the Sonny & Cher duo was formed, Sonny Bono and Cherilyn made music together.

In May 1965, Cher released her debut single, titled "All I Really Want to Do".

On August 16, 1965, Cher released her debut album, titled "All I Really Want to Do" at age 19.

On September 1, 1971, Cher released her first number one single, titled "Gypsys, Tramps & Thieves".

In 1975, Sonny Bono divorced Cher. She started dating Gregg Allman the same year.

In 1977, The duo between Sonny and Cher was disformed.

In 1979, Gregg Allman divorced Cher.

On January 5, 1998, Sonny Bono died due to a Blunt trauma as a result of a skiing accident at Stateline, Nevada aged 62.[3]

YouTube[]

On September 24, 2005, Cher created her YouTube channel. The first video was uploaded on October 8, 2009, titled "Cher - Love And Understanding".

Content[]

Cher usually makes music.

Trivia[]

Georgia Holt is Cher's mother.

She has 2 children, Chaz Bono and Elijah Blue Allman.

She is usually referred as the "Goddess of Pop".[4]

She is a part of the LGBTQ+ community.[5]
